result.execSummary:
The defendant Tyler Z Steckbauer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt: Sentencing After Revocation/Sentencing Hearing held 4-8-16 - see 15CF58

Defendant Tyler Z Steckbauer in court & in custody with attorney Andrew M. Morgan.  Galen Bayne-Allison appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court calls 15CF58, 15CF85, 16CF23  @ 3:15 pm. 15CF58 & 15CF85 for sentencing after revocation, & 16CF23 for plea & sentencing.  16CF23 State gives plea agreement, ct 1 & 3 plea, ct 2 DRI, ct 1 & 3 on each ct's withheld sentence 4 years probation, costs only, AODA & counseling. 15CF58 & 15CF85 will proceed with  Atty Morgan does not agree with agreement in 16CF23 so can't proceed today. Recess @ 3:19 pm. Reconvene @ 3:52 pm.  Parties had off the record discussion.  State has not changed plea agreement, 2 years initial confinement  3 years extended supervision,  70 days credit 15CF58 & 15CF85 jail ordered.  Atty Morgan agrees with plea agreement, all sentences concurrent with each other.  15CF58 & 15CF85 Atty Morgan has received revocation summary, no corrections.  State also has copy and no corrections. Victim rights have been complied with in 15CF85. 16CF23 - Plea questionnaire & waiver of rights filed. Def. understands charges & penalties Ct 1 Poss of Meth, repeater, Guilty plea & Ct 3 Bailjumping, Guilty, Ct 2 DRI, Def. advised of constitutional rights & J.T. rights.  Def. understands elements. Def. admits prior convictions.  Atty Morgan is satisfied.  Court finds pleas are freely & voluntarily given.  Factual basis stipulated.  Court finds factual basis, accept pleas & finds def. Guilty to Poss of Meth. repeater in ct 1 & Bailjumping, repeater in ct 3. State gives sentencing recommendation on 3 files. Atty Morgan gives sentencing recommendation. Def. has nothing to say. Court gives ruling & orders 
15CF58 ct 1 5 years prison, 2 years initial confinement & 3 years extended supervision, Def. is eligible for Challenge Program & Substance Abuse Program. 70 days credit, All court obligations to be converted to civil judgment. 
15CF85 ct 1 9 months jail concurrent to 15CF58, ct 2 90 days jail, concurrent to ct 1 & 15CF58, 67 days credit, time served. All court obligations converted to civil judgment.
16CF23 Ct's 1 & 3 withheld prison sentence, 4 years probation, costs only on each ct, 250 DNA Surcharge on each ct. Def. advised of firearm & voting rights.  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Def. advised of postconviction rights. DNA sample already provided. Def. makes statement.
